headline: Can Intel’s New Arizona Chip Fab Bring It Back From The Brink?
summary: Intel is now in high-volume production of its latest chip node, 18A, at a new Arizona fab it hopes will compete with TSMC. But so far, no major external customers are making on 18A. Following years of missteps, Intel faces an uphill battle to regain customer trust. In the meantime, its received billions from Nvidia, SoftBank and the U.S. government - which took a 10% stake in the company. CNBC got the first ever on-camera tour inside Fab52 and asked its foundry head why this time, it won’t fail.

headline: Are Intel's (INTC) Leadership Shifts And AI Rumors Quietly Rewriting Its Washington Strategy?
summary: In recent days, Intel announced senior leadership changes across government affairs, marketing, and advanced technology strategy, while also facing fresh scrutiny from U.S. lawmakers over its evaluation of China-linked chipmaking equipment and sitting at the center of growing AI acquisition rumors involving SambaNova. Together, these developments highlight how Intel is trying to deepen its influence in Washington and accelerate its AI ambitions even as regulatory and geopolitical risks...
